calls.name: CancelMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Cancel a matchmaking ticket.
calls.requestDetails: Only servers and ticket members can cancel a ticket. The ticket can be in four different states when it is cancelled. 1: the ticket is waiting for members to join it, and it has not started matching. If the ticket is cancelled at this stage, it will never match. 2: the ticket is matching. If the ticket is cancelled, it will stop matching. 3: the ticket is matched. A matched ticket cannot be cancelled. 4: the ticket is already cancelled and nothing happens. There may be race conditions between the ticket getting matched and the client making a cancellation request. The client must handle the possibility that the cancel request fails if a match is found before the cancellation request is processed. We do not allow resubmitting a cancelled ticket because players must consent to enter matchmaking again. Create a new ticket instead.

calls.summary: Gets the status of whether a title is enabled for the multiplayer server feature.
calls.requestDetails: Gets the status of whether a title is enabled for the multiplayer server feature. The enabled status can be Initializing, Enabled, and Disabled.

calls.name: JoinMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Join a matchmaking ticket.
calls.requestDetails: Add the player to a matchmaking ticket and specify all of its matchmaking attributes. Players can join a ticket if and only if their EntityKeys are already listed in the ticket's Members list. The matchmaking service automatically starts matching the ticket against other matchmaking tickets once all players have joined the ticket. It is not possible to join a ticket once it has started matching.

calls.name: ListAssetSummaries
calls.summary: Lists multiplayer server game assets for a title.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of multiplayer server game asset summaries for a title.

calls.name: ListBuildSummaries
calls.summary: Lists summarized details of all multiplayer server builds for a title.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of summarized details of all multiplayer server builds for a title.

calls.name: ListCertificateSummaries
calls.summary: Lists multiplayer server game certificates for a title.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of multiplayer server game certificates for a title.

calls.name: ListMatchmakingQueues
calls.summary: List all matchmaking queue configs.
calls.requestDetails: Gets a list of all the matchmaking queue configurations for the title.

calls.name: ListMultiplayerServers
calls.summary: Lists multiplayer server sessions for a build.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of multiplayer servers for a build in a specific region.

calls.name: ListQosServers
calls.summary: Lists quality of service servers.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of quality of service servers.

calls.name: ListVirtualMachineSummaries
calls.summary: Lists virtual machines for a title.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of virtual machines for a title.

calls.name: RemoveMatchmakingQueue
calls.summary: Remove a matchmaking queue config.
calls.requestDetails: Deletes the configuration for a queue. This will permanently delete the configuration and players will no longer be able to match in the queue. All outstanding matchmaking tickets will be cancelled.

calls.name: RequestMultiplayerServer
calls.summary: Request a multiplayer server session.
calls.requestDetails: Requests a multiplayer server session from a particular build in any of the given preferred regions.

calls.name: SetMatchmakingQueue
calls.summary: Create or update a matchmaking queue configuration.
calls.requestDetails: Use this API to create or update matchmaking queue configurations. The queue configuration defines the matchmaking rules. The matchmaking service will match tickets together according to the configured rules. Queue resources are not spun up by calling this API. Queues are created when the first ticket is submitted.

calls.name: ShutdownMultiplayerServer
calls.summary: Shuts down a multiplayer server session.
calls.requestDetails: Executes the shutdown callback from the GSDK and terminates the multiplayer server session. The callback in the GSDK will allow for graceful shutdown with a 15 minute timeoutIf graceful shutdown has not been completed before 15 minutes have elapsed, the multiplayer server session will be forcefully terminated on it's own.

calls.name: UpdateBuildRegions
calls.summary: Updates a multiplayer server build's regions.
calls.requestDetails: Updates a multiplayer server build's regions.

calls.name: UploadCertificate
calls.summary: Uploads a multiplayer server game certificate.
calls.requestDetails: Uploads a multiplayer server game certificate.
